# LeakSanitizer suppressions for the Foundry Local C++ SDK.
#
# Each line is of the form:   leak:<symbol-or-library-substring>
# A leak is suppressed when the substring matches any frame of the leak's
# stack trace (or, with `leak:<libname>`, the library that allocated it).
#
# These suppressions are read by run_sanitizer_tests.py via
#   LSAN_OPTIONS=suppressions=<this file>
#
# When to add an entry:
#   - ONNX Runtime and ONNX Runtime GenAI commonly leak first-use thread-local
#     caches, EP singletons, and TLS arenas at process exit. These are not
#     bugs in foundry_local; suppress them so real leaks in src/ stand out.
#   - Add the *narrowest* substring that matches the noisy frame — prefer a
#     fully-qualified symbol (`onnxruntime::Foo::Bar`) over a library name.
#
# Examples (uncomment and adjust as you discover real noise):
#   # leak:onnxruntime::Environment
#   # leak:OrtGetApiBase
#   # leak:Ort::Global
#   # leak:Generators::OgaHandle
#   # leak:libonnxruntime.so

# --- libcurl OpenSSL session cache: handle outlives the test process.
leak:Curl_ossl_add_session
leak:Curl_ssl_scache_create
leak:cf_ssl_scache_peer_init

# --- Azure SDK: process-static CURLSH wrapper.
leak:CURLSHWrapper

# --- ORT GenAI C++ wrapper bug: OgaMultiModalProcessor::Process{Images,Audios,
# ImagesAndAudios}(vector<const char*>, ...) overloads in ort_genai.h allocate
# an OgaStringArray via OgaCreateStringArrayFromStrings but never call
# OgaDestroyStringArray on it. Fixed upstream in ort.genai (D:\src\github\ort.genai);
# remove this suppression once the SDK consumes a release containing the fix.
# https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime-genai/pull/2153
leak:OgaCreateStringArrayFromStrings

# --- ORT GenAI C++ wrapper bug: OrtxTensorResultGetAt (in onnxruntime-extensions) which returns a
# heap-allocated TensorObject that the C++ wrapper never releases via OrtxDispose. 
# remove this suppression once the SDK consumes a release containing the fix.
# https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime-genai/pull/2168
leak:OrtxTensorResultGetAt

# --- ORT GenAI bug: Generators::State::Run calls OrtSession::Run with an
# OrtValue** output array but the State never releases the returned output
# handles, leaking one OrtValue (24 B) plus its backing tensor buffers
# (multi-MB per call) for every Run. Observed across audio streaming tests.
# Remove once the SDK consumes a release containing the upstream fix.
# This is the source of the onnxruntime allocated leaks. Can be verified by 
# running with `--integration-only --gtest_filter=StreamingAudioFixture.\*`
# https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime-genai/pull/2169
leak:Generators::State::Run